postcontent:
Our # XML913

Restrictions apply on high capacity magazines in some jurisdictions, so please read this entire ad carefully before offering to buy. This listing is for THREE Magazines. Hit Buy It Once, and you’re buying 3, not 1. Hit Buy It 3 times, and you’re buying 9, and so on. Buyers can take any number of extras we have available at the same per-mag price and no additional shipping charges. Here are Lorcin factory magazines for their model L9 pistols. Manufacturer was Lorcin Engineering of Mira Loma, California. Construction is blue steel body, steel springs, aluminum alloy cartridge follower, and black anodized alloy finger rest type floor plate. Each magazine will hold 13 rounds of 9mm ammunition. These were manufactured during the infamous period that began in 1994 and ended in 2004, when 13 shot magazines could not be sold on the civilian market. Since Lorcin was literally gunning for overseas markets, these had to be marked Export Only. That is a moot issue since 2004 in most jurisdictions of the United States. These magazines will only work in a Lorcin model L9 pistol that accepts double stacked magazines. They will not work in an L9C Compact; Will Not work in a Hi-Point; Will Not work on a John Deere 47H Manure Spreader. They will only work on a Lorcin Industries model L9 pistol. Lorcin, of course, is long gone out of business, so when these are gone, there won’t be any more. These magazines have been stored for several years. They have never been loaded or issued; they do, however, show contact wear on their edges from being stored in bulk. We found them in an old Atlantic Warehouse. Our single magazine price is $29 per. title: For Sale:  AR15 & 870 & Mosin
location: Mount Airy, Winston Salem, North Carolina
postcontent:
Looking to sell a few different things.

 First is a built AR 15. The main things are full mil spec 16 inch medium contour barrel with diamond fluting and 1/7 twist rate carbine gas system. ALG trigger free floated diamond head VRS-T rail.YHM upper Spikes lower. Magpul MS3 sling. BCM Gunfighter edition Mod 4 charging handle. Springco Blue Spring. ST-T2 buffer. Troy Claymore muzzle brake. All that results in a very soft and very very fast firing reliable rifle. I frog lubbed the BCG and charging handle so it runs very very smooth. Price is $2000. Text me for a full on parts list and some details and pictures.

Second is a Magpul Edition 870. Comes with everything from the factory. Magpul furniture, risers, LoP spacers. Adjustable  XS ghost ring sights. Top mounted picitanny rail for optics. Full on cerakoted black. Added a Mesa Tactical 6 shot side saddle mounted properly to the reciever. Brand new they are about 720 + tax = 820 + the side saddle = 900. I'm asking 750. Mine is practically brand new. Would trade a 1100 Tactical but thats probably about it. Maybe a nice 1911.

Ex Sniper Mosin Nagant. Full matching numbers very good bore good rifling. Bayonet included. Smooth bolt. Also has a high front post. I've only fired a few rounds through it but cleaned it every time I went out with it. $180

Stripped Spikes Tactical non color filed Honey Badger lower. New never used. Bought it and put it in the safe. $100

I also got a free float YHM XL-Specter length free float quad rail. Used it on a previous rifle for a few months. Took it off and its sat in storage every since. Includes delta ring, barrel nut, cap,and timing screws. $80

Last thing a pair of Oakley Flak Jacket XLJ's. Matte black frames and transition lenses. I bought these somewhere around a year ago from the SI website. I don't think they are selling the transition lenses anymore (or at least right now). Frame has a little play in them but still pretty good off. Includes a hard shell Oakley case and cleaning cloth and an extra pair of nose pieces. They make very very good shooting glasses. Pretty much the only thing I've used them for. Can wear them in sunshine, rain, or snow. From dawn till dusk. $140

Call or text me at REDACTED for more info. I'll gladly send pictures or answer any questions. Apparently the pictures my phone takes are too big to post on armslist.

The HellFighter® WeaponLight for crew-served weapons and heavy guns packs power and versatility into a tough, compact package that weighs only 10 pounds and measures a mere eight inches in length. It features a blinding 3,000-lumen beam with enough reach to illuminate targets hundreds of yards away and enough surround beam to make it perfect for patrol or search-and-rescue operations. 

Built to withstand intense recoil and combat conditions, the HellFighter's water-resistant body is constructed from high-strength aerospace aluminum with a Mil-Spec Type III hard anodizing finish. A 5mm multi-coated Pyrex® window protects its lamp assembly, and the window itself is protected from dust, mud, and heavy particle impact by either a swing-open amber filter for cutting through smoke or dust, a swing-open infrared for use with night vision devices (NVDs), or a swing-open opaque cover. 

The HellFighter's rugged high-intensity discharge (HID) lamp is powered by one or two military BA-5590 batteries or from a 12-volt auto battery, and is virtually immune to failure from recoil, vibration, or impact since it has no filament to break or burn out.
